This installs Hyprland with a default config: `~/.config/hypr/hyprland.conf`

<br/>

### Keyboard Language
Hyprland uses a setting in config file, defaulting to `US`:

`input { kb_layout = us }`

<br/>

### Monitors
```
monitor=,preferred,auto,auto
```

<br/>

Format is: `monitor = <name>, <resolution>, <position>, <scale>`

- empty `<name>` uses first found/default
- Show monitors info: `hyprctl monitors all`

<br/>

### Keybindings 

Defined towards the end of the file, they are the 'Windows' key + another:

<br/>

|Key|Function|App|
|:---:|:---|:---|
|E|file manager|dolphin|
|Q|terminal|kitty|
|R|launcher|wofi|
|C|close active window|-|
|M|exit hyprland|-|